<TITLE> FAO to start project for cyclone victims </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 26 (bdnews24.com)  The UN Food and Agricultural Organisation (FAO) will take up a project to support livelihoods of cyclone victims. The $16 million 4-year WB-funded rehabilitation programme will be conducted in 13 upazilas in Khulna and Barisal, affected by Sidr and Aila cyclones. Speaking at an agreement signing ceremony to that effect, the FAO representative, Ad Spijkers said the activities would be for agricultural and livelihood development for rehabilitation of Sidr victims. "Farmers need support to restore their livelihood and restore agricultural production." Spijkers said the project would enhance farmers' production with improved inputs. "This project will enhance farmers' production systems through improved seeds, fertilisers, storage and irrigation." The project will also help fishermen and aquaculture farmers and livestock rearers, he said. FAO will implement one component of the emergency recovery and restoration project, introducing new technologies to improve the resilience of communities and households in cyclone prone areas. The signing ceremony was attended by the planning minister, AK Khandker, planning secretary Habib Ullah Majumder and among ot
